    <briefdescription>
<para>An <ref refid="class_hd_repr" kindref="compound">HdRepr</ref> refers to a (single) topological representation of an rprim, and owns the draw item(s) that visually represent it. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The draw items are populated by the rprim. The relevant compositional hierarchy is:</para>
<para><ref refid="class_hd_rprim" kindref="compound">HdRprim</ref> | +<ndash/><ref refid="class_hd_repr" kindref="compound">HdRepr(s)</ref> | +<ndash/><ref refid="class_hd_draw_item" kindref="compound">HdDrawItem(s)</ref></para>
<para>When multiple topological representations are required for an rprim, we use <ref refid="class_hd_repr_selector" kindref="compound">HdReprSelector</ref> to compose the individual representations. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
